        <name>referencePoint</name>
        <qualifiedname>MR::Features::Primitives::ConeSegment::referencePoint</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Some point on the axis, but not necessarily the true center point. Use <computeroutput><ref refid="structMR_1_1Features_1_1Primitives_1_1ConeSegment_1a9f96764db5c4750b318539f5c7ccf9b3" kindref="member">centerPoint()</ref></computeroutput> for that. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sanity requirements:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>dir</computeroutput> must be normalized.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Both <computeroutput>positiveLength</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>negativeLength</computeroutput> should be non-negative. They can be infinite (both or individually).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If they are equal (both zero) or at least one of them is infinite, <computeroutput>positiveSideRadius</computeroutput> must be equal to <computeroutput>negativeSideRadius</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Both <computeroutput>positiveSideRadius</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>negativeSideRadius</computeroutput> must be non-negative. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
